               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="INS0039MY">Dabra Maʿṣo</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1600" notAfter="1671">Seventeenth century, possibly
                        first half or around the middle.</origDate>
                        The manuscript was commissioned for the church of <placeName ref="INS0039MY">Dabra Maʿḍo Yohannǝs</placeName>by
                        <persName ref="PRS13124GabraKrestos">Gabra Krǝstos</persName>, a son of
                           priest Sǝmʿon from Dabra Maʿḍo (s. <ref target="#coloph1"/> and <ref target="#coloph2"/>), and written by three scribes,
                           one of them being <persName ref="PRS13119FequraIyasus">Fǝqura Iyasus</persName> (his name and
                           affiliation are provided with slight deviations in the colophons). It cannot be excluded that
                         the part of the manuscript with <ref target="#ms_i1"/> was planned or produced and used as
                         a circulation unit, and somewhat later expanded with texts dedicated to <persName ref="PRS5741Johnthe">John the Baptist</persName>.
                           The name of <persName ref="PRS13123TaklaEwostatewos">Takla ʾEwosṭatewos, the governer (<foreign xml:lang="gez">sǝyyum</foreign>) of Dabra Maʿḍo </persName>,
                           is written in the supplication formulas over erasures (e.g., on <locus target="#3ra"/>, <locus target="#6va"/>).
                          The monk <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS13125ZabanaKrestos">Zabāna Krǝstos</persName> (attested for <date>1664-71</date>) later added
                          concluding supplications with his own name on some folia (<locus target="#8ra"/>, <locus target="#28vb"/>,
                          <locus target="#30va"/>, <locus target="#33ra"/>, <locus target="#34vb"/>,
                          <locus target="#39vb"/>), and two miracles <ref target="#ms_i1.2.31"/> and <ref target="#ms_i1.2.32"/>.
                          </origin>
               </history>
